comment.author: 92723869@N07
comment._content: Vehicle #599 could possibly be a model-T, but judging by the shape of the radiator, the vehicle facing the photographer is not. That radiator shape was fairly common at the time and would date the vehicle to around 1910-12. The O-class tram #964 came into service sometime between 1908 and 1914. So I would suggest  that this photo was taken around 1912-14. By 1920 there most probably would have been a few more cars on the road than the 3 visible in this photo.
